TCS NextStep Portal
Welcome aboard on TCS NextStep portal!

TCS NextStep Portal is the first step connecting you with TCS, Asia's leading IT services Company. A single platform that addresses all your needs interactively and simplifies the communication process, this Portal will help you in your transition from being a student on campus to exploring a dynamic career path with TCS.

From keeping you updated on TCS initiatives to answering your queries and helping you explore a world of opportunities, TCS NextStep helps bridge the distance in your journey to becoming a TCSer.

So, go ahead! Explore opportunities. Experience Certainty.
Your candidature/application is subject to fulfillment of the TCS eligibility criteria as specified below:

  • Minimum aggregate (aggregate of ALL subjects in ALL semesters) marks of 60% or above in the first attempt in each of your Class Xth, Class XIIth, Diploma (if applicable), Graduation and Post-Graduation examination which includes successful completion of your final year/semester without any pending arrears/back logs during the entire course duration. Please note that all subjects mentioned on the mark sheets should be taken into consideration while calculating the aggregate marks. For example, best of 5/6 subjects for calculating the aggregate is not acceptable as per the TCSL Eligibility Criteria. All subjects mentioned on the marksheet (including languages, optional subjects etc) should be taken into consideration for calculating obtained/total marks/CGPA.

  • First attempt implies that you should pass the final year/semester examination (Xth, XIIth, Diploma, Graduation and Post-Graduation as applicable) with minimum aggregate (aggregate of all subjects in all semesters) marks of 60% and above within the normal duration of the course itself.For example, if you have secured 58.9 % (aggregate of all subjects) in your Standard XIIth examination in the first attempt and you have taken an improvement exam in the next attempt securing 62 %, you do not fulfil the TCSL eligibility criteria as marks/CGPA obtained during the normal duration of the course only will be considered.

  • Completion of all courses Class Xth onwards within the stipulated time as specified by your University/Institute and as per the TCSL Selection Guidelines without any extended education. For example, if you have a backlog in the final semester of BE, it is considered as extended education as the stipulated time to complete BE is 4 years.
  • It is mandatory to declare the gaps/arrears/backlogs, if any, during your academic and work experience. Break in education should not be due to extended education. Any break in education/work experience should not exceed 24 months.

  • Only Full time courses will be considered.

  • You should be minimum 18 years of age to be eligible to apply for the TCS Selection process.

  • Candidates who have applied to TCS and have not been successful in clearing the TCSL selection process, are not eligible to re-apply to TCS within six months from the date on which they had attended such selection test and/or interview. You are not eligible to appear for the TCS selection process within six months of the previous unsuccessful attempt.

TCS Offerings

  1. IT

    2. TCS IT Services provides best-in-class solutions to address the IT needs of an enterprise. It delivers excellence and certainty by providing application development and management, testing, system integration services and solutions. It covers a full spectrum of end-to-end services in:
    • Custom Application Development
    • Application Maintenance and Production support
    • Application Modernisation
    • System Integration
    • Performance Engineering

    For more information,visit http://www.tcs.com/offerings/it-services.
  2. EIS

    3. TCS Engineering & Industrial Services (EIS) is a holistic service line which comprises of:
    • Engineering design of any product through "Product Design Services" (includes Electro-mechanical design, Embedded hardware and software design and Product validation)
    • Improving manufacturing process of Discrete and Process Industries through its "Plant Solutions and Services" (includes Plant Design, Plant Automation, Control Systems Integration, Manufacturing Execution Systems and Asset Management)
    • Supporting digitisation through "Product Development IT Services" (includes Product Life-cycle Management solutions, Engineering and R&D tools management)

    For more information,visit https://www.tcs.com/offerings/engineering_services.
  3. Research

    4. TCS Research explores new ideas in Software Engineering, Applications and Systems. It supports both invention and innovation. TCS research also creates pilots and proofs of concepts for customers which involve shaping new ideas around leading edge technologies into agile applications. It offers an opportunity to work with world class researchers.
    For more information,visit http://www.tcs.com/research.
  4. IT IS

    5. TCS IT Infrastructure Services (IT IS) s a horizontal unit in TCS that serves the dynamic infrastructure requirements across various vertical domains. IT IS provides:
    • End user computing services, which manages end-user infrastructure remotely, develops in-house tools, leverages services of strong alliances and provides support services.
    • IT Service Desk, which is a single point of contact for IT related issues
    • Data Centre Services, which involves proactive monitoring and management services, data centre consolidation, migration and automation services, virtualisation and cloud services, hosting services and Green data centre services
    • IT Service Management, which assesses process maturity and operating models against ISO20000 / ITIL best practices, designs and implements ITIL V3 compliant processes and tools platform, and so on.

    For more information,visit https://www.tcs.com/offerings/it_infrastructure.
